Andrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran were the ringleaders of the Bali Nine drug cartel . 
  The pair were convicted in 2005 of smuggling heroin out of Indonesia . 
  Both men were disillusioned by their jobs and attracted to the promise of riches . 
  Their legal appeals and pleas for clemency have been rejected . 
  The men were caught in 2005 trying to smuggle eight kilograms of heroin . 
 